# Git commit author email

When creating commits in this workspace, use the author email that matches where the code will be pushed:

- **GitHub** (e.g. `github.com`, remotes named `origin` pointing at GitHub): set and use **`charu2722001@gmail.com`**.
  - For a GitHub-only repo: `git config user.email "charu2722001@gmail.com"` in that repository (local config is fine).

- **Azure DevOps** (e.g. `dev.azure.com`, ADO remotes): set and use **`charu.jain@ril.com`**.
  - For an Azure DevOps–only repo: `git config user.email "charu.jain@ril.com"` in that repository.

Before committing, if unsure which remote applies, check `git remote -v` and match the host. Never mix emails for the same remote by mistake.
